.TH "DESKLAUNCH" "1" "2026-05-21"
.PP
.SH NAME
.PP
desklaunch - launch a .\&desktop file
.PP
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\fBdesklaunch\fR [\fB-p\fR] <path>
.PP
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Reads the .\&desktop file at \fIpath\fR, strips field codes from the Exec
line, and runs the command in the background.\&
.PP
With the \fB-p\fR flag the command is printed to stdout instead of
executed.\& This is useful for inspecting the command or piping it to
another tool.\&
.PP
Both modes update the shared history file, which affects ordering in
\fBlsdesktop\fR(1).\&
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
\fB-p\fR
.RS 4
Print the cleaned exec command.\& Do not run it.\&
.PP
.RE
.SH FILES
.PP
\fI$HOME/.\&cache/lsdesktop/history\fR
.RS 4
Shared launch history.\& Written by \fBdesklaunch\fR, read by
\fBlsdesktop\fR(1).\&
.PP
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.PP
\fB0\fR
.RS 4
Success.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB1\fR
.RS 4
Usage error, missing argument, or command failure.\&
.PP
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
\fBlsdesktop\fR(1), \fBdesktop-file-validate\fR(1)
.PP
